com.hoovler.dao.impl

Class DefaultProfileDao

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hoovler.dao.impl.DefaultProfileDao
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProfileDao

    public class DefaultProfileDao
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProfileDao
    The default implementation of the ProfileDao interface.

    Examples

    Instantiate a new, empty DAO object:

    ProfileDao profileDao = new DefaultProfileDao();
    ProfileDao profileDao = new DefaultProfileDao(false);

    Instantiate a new DAO object auto-populated with the default data source:

    ProfileDao profileDao = new DefaultProfileDao(true);

    Instantiate a new DAO object using a custom URI data source:

    String dataSource = "http://your.custom.domain/api/profiles";
    ProfileDao profileDao = new DefaultProfileDao(dataSource);
    See Also:

      • DefaultProfileDao

        public DefaultProfileDao(boolean autoPopulate)
        Instantiates a new DefaultProfileDao object based on the autoPopulate boolean value.

        If autoPopulate is true, this constructor will:

        1. First checks for the URL in the value of the json.url.default within /resources/profile_dao.properties
        2. If unavailable, it the used the hard-coded value of https://www.willowtreeapps.com/api/v1.0/profiles

        If autoPopulate is false, this acts like the default constructor.

        To manually set a data source URL, use the following constructor instead: 

        DefaultProfileDao profileDao = new DefaultProfileDao(jsonUrl)
